Example usage with backtrace:<p><pre><code>    set -o errtrace
    trap &#x27;err_handler $?&#x27; ERR

    err_handler() {
      trap - ERR
      let i=0 exit_status=$1
      echo &quot;Aborting on error $exit_status:&quot;
      echo &quot;--------------------&quot;
      while caller $i; do ((i++)); done
      exit $?
    }</code></pre>

It&#x27;s Perl. The last `$_`; evals what&#x27;s in $_, so change it to just print the variable:<p><pre><code>  $_=&#x27;^#(/||/@!@[{@:^[-[&#x27;^&quot;;@@@\\>])@.&quot;.
  &quot;{)/];)^{&quot;;$,+=(++$,);$_.=&quot;>&$,&quot;;
  print &quot;$_&quot;;
</code></pre>
The output is:<p><pre><code>  echo Brian Rogers >&2</code></pre>
